cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of predicting salient regions in natural scenes using eye-tracking data. This is a problem that is commonly studied in the computer vision community, and specifically in the subfield of computer vision that deals with image and video analysis, which is represented by the cs.CV category. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to learn the weights of different feature maps and viewing patterns, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also deals with human-computer interaction, as it aims to improve the performance of saliency models by taking into account the time-dependent nature of visual exploration, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses eye-tracking data, which is a common tool in the field of multimedia (cs.MM).
